John Charles, Makurdi A former Commissioner of Police in the Lagos State Police Command, Alhaji Abubakar Tsav, was on Monday buried at a public cemetery in Makurdi, Benue State, according to Muslim rites. Tsav died on Monday at Federal Medical Centre, Makurdi, Benue State capital. He was 81 years old and was survived by wife and seven children. His remains were brought to  Central Mosque, Wadata in Makurdi and left for  public cementary after the 4pm prayer. He was later interred around 4.55pm at the public cemetery. Tsav was best known as a former CP of Lagos command. He, however, served as Federal Commissioner of Public Complaint Commission in Benue State till 2019. Meanwhile, the state governor, Samuel Ortom, has commiserated with his family. In a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Terver Akase, Ortom described Tsav as a gallant officer during his years in service. The statement read in part, “The governor expresses shock at the demise of Alhaji Tsav whom he describes as a gallant police officer during his years in service. He prayed God to grant the deceased eternal rest and his family, the fortitude to bear the loss.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 